The 1984 general election in [Puerto Rico](/Puerto_Rico) thus marked a clear mandate for the [Popular Democratic Party](/Popular_Democratic_Party_(Puerto_Rico)) and [Rafael Hernández Colón](/Rafael_Hern%C3%A1ndez_Col%C3%B3n), ushering in a period of unified government control. Whether this translated into a more effective or merely more consistent governance is, of course, a matter for historians to debate and for the perpetually optimistic to hope for.

